<BaseLayout title="Company | BeaconGuard Assurance">
  <section>
    <h1>Company</h1>
  <p>BeaconGuard Assurance builds enterprise governance infrastructure for AI runtime operations and financial workflow control boundaries.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Mission</h2>
    <p>
      Our mission is to make AI authorization dependable, reviewable, and operationally practical with bounded trust.
      BeaconGuard reduces ambiguity by separating deterministic policy control, enforcement, and evidence generation
      into a clear fail-closed runtime boundary.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What the company is building</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard is building control-layer infrastructure for financial institutions evaluating AI in sensitive workflows.
      The product helps architecture, security, risk, and operational teams review whether AI interactions are allowed to proceed under governed policy.
      The company is focused on practical control boundaries, fail-closed behavior, and reviewable evidence.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Why BeaconGuard exists</h2>
    <p>
      Enterprises want to adopt AI in sensitive workflows, but model behavior is probabilistic.
      Control ownership, auditability, and policy enforcement cannot be left to prompt design alone.
      BeaconGuard exists to provide a deterministic control boundary and reviewable evidence layer around those workflows.
    </p>
  </section>

